reviews.text: Came in within the last hour before they closed. Got the pizza and pasta. Both delivered in flavor and consistency. Desert was one of the best! Will have to come back for their lobster specials. Overall amazing service. :)

Sorry to say that my experience here was disappointing. I had read good things about this place and we were there at a busy time on a Saturday evening which may have contributed to the problems, but I do think they should be able to handle the pressure of a busy weekend evening. We shared the Fritto Misto as an appetizer and it was well prepared, delicately fried, came out promptly with a tasty red sauce. I had the Cacio a Pepe pasta as my main course. The dish came out cold and the sauce was kind of watery and the proportions were off.
We also ordered the asparagus as a side dish and it never came. My husband had to the mushroom risotto which used ordinary button mushrooms and it was underwhelming.

In fairness, the hostess gave us two complementary glasses of wine as an apology for the poor service and she also brought out the asparagus and didn’t charge us although we were almost finished with our meal by then. At least she made a sincere effort to try to set things right. Other than that, it is a pleasant room and appears to be quite popular. Hopefully they will get the service issues straightened out.

Via Ghibellina is an awesome hidden gem and was a perfect addition to an Italian themed evening in DC for my husband and I.  We were in the area tasting Italian liqueurs at Don Ciccio and Figli and were ready for dinner.  We walked around the block and decided to stop in here.  The restaurant is rather unassuming from outside, but as soon as we walked in we were warmly greeted and shown to our table.  Everyone we interacted with on the staff was very kind.  One gentlemen by the name of Rodrigo, I believe, asked what our general preferences were for Italian food and then gave great recommendations.  I noticed he was attentive to all the tables in this manner, which was really great to see.  It should be noted this is a small to average sized establishment and was moderately busy while we were there. We ordered caprese to start accompanied by Chianti and then two homemade pasta dishes (beef with noodles and lamb with noodles) for our entrees.  They also gave us homemade bread that was a perfect compliment to the caprese.  Everything was very fresh and delicious.  What may seem like rather simple dishes were distinctly flavorful and well put together.  We ordered tiramisu for dessert and while I would have like the lady fingers a little more soaked in espresso, it was still really good.  I would definitely come back and you should give this place a chance the next time you are in the neighborhood.  Thanks!  :-)

Had an amazing dinner here at Via Ghibellina! Super lovely restaurant in Ivy City near Planet Fitness and Mom’s.

This is some of the best and most authentic Italian we’ve had yet in the city. We got the arancini appetizer and they gave a DELICIOUS flatbread with it as well. I got the house Chardonnay, which was good, though a little more light than I wanted.

For meals, we got the pappardelle con ragú di agnello (braised lamb, green olives, tomato, grana padano and mint) and pici alla carretiera (garlic, olive oil, light spicy tomato sauce, pepperoncino, basil). Both were amazing, though I think both us agree the pappardelle took the crown for the night. The pici was wonderful, but maybe slightly too spicy. Be cautious if you’re not big into spice on that dish!

Aside from the food, the service was incredible. Everyone was kind and genuine. One of the staff there actually saw that our table was a little wobbly upon sitting, and immediately asked to fix it for us.

We will gladly be returning and highly recommending!
I’d give it more stars if I could. Absolutely fantastic Italian food. Great service, perfect wine recommendations, all in a nice cozy ambience. I highly recommend this place!!

Exceeded expectations. Quality and fresh ingredients cooked directly to order with texture and bright colors. It’s not just rice and beans, but rice and beans done right with unique additions and flavors added in. Would’ve liked more shrimp per order but the whole plate is a step, if not two, beyond typical flavors in this cuisine! Looking forward to trying more of their wide variety in the future.

Great ambiance, but the food is very lacks flavor. Interestingly, at 2pm on a weekday there were no customers in the restaurant.  Normally in DC a place would have a line or at least people sitting at the tables.

This is Tex-Mex  In no way is this authentic Spanish food (they don't claim to be).  Bland meat and old rice.  Mozzarella cheese is standard for fajitas?   Meat has grissle and was cooked for all of about 3 minutes. Terribly bland but I taste lots of soy sauce. A couple of steps up from Taco Bell.

I do not recommend.  There are a number of places on the block less expensive and with way better food.

Thanks for looking!
Great place i go here weekly i recommend one of their cabos
There are many varieties of salad, I recommend it.
good food

This is by far the fastest Papa John's I  the DMV. I've ordered 3 times and I swear the pizza is so hot when it arrives that it burns my mouth.
It's difficult to find places in Northeast that consistently perform up to expectations. This Papa John's is definitely one of the places to go to
They brought me the wrong pizza, promised they'd be back in 10 minutes with the right order and never came back.

The pizza was soggy is hell, you can tell they stretch the pie to much. Wasn't cooked all the way thru was not how I ask. that was the 2nd time my order was wrong an that will be the last time I order from that location again.
Delicious and super fast delivery! Everything looks good! Pizza, wings, and the cinnamon pull aparts!
You all have one job..... My pizza is burnt. THIS IS RIDICULOUS

This little Neapolitan pizza place is amazing! I went for on a busy Saturday for lunch. There was only one staff but the waiter was so efficient and friendly. Pizzas were so delicious and the portions were big enough for me to bring half home. The Cappuccino Truffle is like an ice cream with coffee truffle in the center of the ice cream ball. It was pretty unique and tasty!

Brought my whole family here, two daughters,  2 son-in-laws, 3 grand kids. Very close to the taste of pizzas in Naples, Italy. Fast service and excellent taste. Antipasto tray good to. The serve Menabrea beer from Italy oldest brewery in Northern Italy. Looks to be dog friendly as well.

I had been hearing good things about this pizza and knew I had to give it a try. Every aspect was delicious: the sauce, the cheese, and the crust. From my experience in Italy, I think it is some of the most authentic Italian pizza that I have had in this area. My one thing for next time is that I will ask for them to spread more sauce and cheese on or get some extra sauce for dipping the crust. There was a lot more plain crust than I prefer, but it should be an easy thing to get around when I go back.

Great place for pizza in Washington DC !For a family of six the bill came to 90 dollars! We ordered a Caprese salad and a Formaggi Della casa plus three pizzas! Food is excellent and we enjoyed the dinner!
Tip: they closed at nine pm and hence do go early to enjoy your meal at leisure

Authentic Napoletana pizza. Warm and friendly neighborhood atmosphere with excellent service. This is the new favorite spot for my husband and I. I wish I could keep it a secret, but the food is so good and you can tell the staff works really hard and takes pride in what they serve. Really enjoyed my experience here and we will be back to try more pizzas.

Went in to checkout new menu.  Staff was impatient because  I had too many questions and could not make up my mind. Only three customers in store at the time (11:30am). I left without making a purchase.  IF I decide to go back I will  definitely  checkout menu online before returning
It's a nice place to eat at, The spacing is small, however, the customer service is very good,  nice and friendly.

It's too hot in there I can't believe whoever owns this would let there business get that hot. You know the food isn't being kept cold..... subway really needs to get it together. Avoid subway go to nearby restaurants!
Seems very cramped inside. Not as busy or as well kept as it used to be. But, my sandwich was good, and the young lady was very polite.
Why did they charge me for a plastic bag?
My pizza was delivered after 2 hours and 22 minutes that was promised between 36-46 minutes. It was cold. Instead of the garlic bread twists I ordered, I got cinnamon twists.

Philly cheesesteak pizza is still the best around. Atmosphere was clean and calm. Manager was very attentive of me. Excellent experience...(PLEASE DO NOT ever take the cheesesteak pizza off the menu ....EVER!!!0

So this isn't an indictment on the staff at all, but on the policy. I called to place an order for pickup at 10:20pm. I'm driving toward the location to pick up pizza and wings for me and my friend. An automated customer service line picked up. Long story short, the automation let's me place an order, confirms what I wanted, tells me the price, then places me on hold.

After placing me hold for 2 minutes, the automated voice says, 'sorry, something went wrong with your order' and hangs up. No other explanation. By this time, I'm close by, so I pulled up and went inside to place the order.

They tell me then that Domino's stops taking pick up orders at 10pm, so they won't take my order. Obviously the register is not closed out, because delivery doesn't stop until midnight. So I'm trying to figure out, why the door is open like I can come in and place an order and why did the automated phone line waste my time? So I said, 'what your telling me is, I can order for delivery while I stand here, but have to go home and wait for you to deliver it? They said yes. So I just walked out and drove to Pizza Bolis nearby.

Yes, I could have ordered it for delivery, sat in my car and just intercepted the pizza when the delivery man came out to deliver to my house. But I was over the experience by then.

This location has never once gotten my order items wrong, which is why I’m sad to write this. But, the treatment that I received from the cashier that was also answering phones the other night was unacceptable. Not only did he personally degrade me when it was his driver in the wrong, he used foul language multiple times toward me repeatedly. After telling the cashier that the delivery person went to a different address, the cashier threatened me and told me that next time I need to put the right address in or I would face consequences. As a business student at a local university, I understand that this type of behavior is not only unprofessional but business and reputation ending. This employee should no longer be representing this store in threatening customers.

I ordered pizza online over a hour ago and still have not left the store. Just cancel the order I don’t understand why you have people waiting for they food I could have came a picked it up by now. Never again will order from this place
Great smoothies here - use the app to get rewards and the first smoothie is for free.
Enjoy getting smoothies here, staff are friendly and professional.
Today I got my hulk but it didn't tasted good as usual another day another time

Went back here and there was 5 kids in the back. Took 3 tries to make my smoothie coorect. The manager came up to fix it. He just added more water then blended it again. Tasted awful!!! Please people most of them don't know what there doing.. get it together. Not going back here!!!!
I order some smoothie today first time really is nasty they didn’t put my items they put on cup like only ice.I requested for people Don’t go over there don’t order in online please.

I came in to the Dunkin Donuts in Rhode Island Row on Sunday 9/25. While waiting for my iced coffee I noticed an employee (younger/female) preparing a food order with no gloves on (which to me is unacceptable). There are two additional things I have issue with: (1) While waiting for the food to cook, this worker walked to the back and began eating and came back chewing with a full mouth (very unprofessional) and (2) proceeded to check if food was cooked by opening oven and touching it with her bare fingers. This is beyond poor customer service and shows a lack of awareness of food handling in a clean manner. I would request that you retrain your employees to ensure customers that they are operating with integrity while providing a service.

I don't like how the store is suppose to be open at a certain time, and nobody is at the front counter to open or even unlock the door! That is ridiculous smh. If I had an option to give your business negative stars, I would've definitely given you a -100 stars. Do better! And have better employees thank you!

This place has got to be THE worst experience I’ve ever had at a Dunkin Donuts!!! Sunday morning, one guy, taking orders, “cooking”, cash register & porter! There’s a line around the corner AND airs more than chilly outside today!!! Never again!!!👎🏻😡

The fact that you can drink a hot beverage and consume food but can't use the bathroom is quite disturbing and I believe absolutely not legal. I will check with the US Attorney General's office to see if that is discrimination. I will also check with DCRA ( DC Department of Refulatory Affairs to see if this is acceptable. If itz not I will surely report them. I don't get this same NO restroom or employee restroom nonsense when I visit other Maryland and Virginia Dunkin Donuts establishments... Must be because the populations skin pigmentation is contains too much melanin.. Yes, I said it. Seems the Black  people aren't deserving g to wash their hands before eating nor clean enough to use the restroom inside. I SHOULD HAVE GIVEN THEM Zero stars, but my friend, well, she enjoyed her coffee..

Easily the worst dunkin I've ever been to. Stopped in for my usual iced coffee and sausage muffin. I ended up with a foul tasting coffee and a croissant.  Coffee didn't even taste like coffee it made my stomach turn.

Completely missed order notes on Uber Eats order, sent me the wrong sized sub and the food looked absolutely disgusting—discolored bread, way too much mayo, overall soggy and completely unappetizing order and presentation despite having paid $20 for an order online. Either they need to do better and management needs to have better oversight or they should be completely prevented from handling online orders since staff obviously cannot follow instructions. Based on that alone, I know the other low-ratings have to be spot on. What an absolute embarrassment of a business.

Clean environment. Friendly staff and fast service. Food was good too. Hours said they closed at 9, but I arrived at 9:06p and was welcomed with no problem.  Not a Jersey Mike's fan but I'd return here.

I don't know what happened to the subs but highly disappointed. It was very thin and very light. I ordered the veggie sub and the one that I got at the Sacramento CA location was fabulous the one in DC not so much😒 For a $20 combo meal, this was not worth it.
I love this spot!  The sandwiches are always right and one of the guys even know what my order is.  Now that's special to me!! Great job team.  All of you deserve a raise.

Generally not a bad restaurant. But today, I'm starving. An hour ago I ordered two sandwiches from here that said they'd be delivered by 5. Over 40 min later I get a notice from Door Dash saying the order was cancelled, no explanation. I tried calling the store and no one picked up.

I'm really hungry and I wish they'd told me sooner.

Great food. I've had the wings, cheesy bacon fries, salad. The customer service is subpar. The workers aren't necessarily rude but there aren't enough. Typically they have the same person cooking and taking orders which causes a delay in ordering and getting anything that you may need from behind the counter (like ranch or ketchup if its not out). Still great food, just know you may have to be patient.

Really cool place the ambiance is amazing I love the boxing theme and all the paintings on the wall.  So many small details in the design of this place that really impressed me.  Service was great!  Had the black bean burger and fries it was really good definitely recommend!

First time trying this place and will never ever eat here again. The cashier is excellent and have awesome customer service, the crispy chicken sandwich on the other hand has me sick as a dog right now. It doesn't say anything about bacon on this sandwich instead it had a raw piece of bacon on it. Well that raw bacon(even though I didn't eat it) has given me food poisoning. I will never eat here again. Thank you but no thank you.

Went here last for dinner ,horrible experience.  My food for 2 persons took approx. An little less the an hour abt 45minuntes. When I got my order it was wrong . Wrong burger, wrong sides. They even ran out of cheddar cheese. Servers where nice and apologetic. But the organization of the restaurant was horrible.  More like a unmanaged moms and pop greasy spoon than an well rounded experience I expected. Disappointed at the experience. Will I visit again? Maybe alone, but as for another casual dinner date night. TOO Burger embarrassed me.

Food was really good the first two times I ate there. But I went there April 1st on a Sunday and my food still wasn't coming to me after 50 minutes. So I made a phone call to try to pass time and you can see employees walking back and forth laughing and staring at me like I'm the one with the problem I seriously just want my food is all so I asked for a refund and 1 other customer asked for one as well which then a lady walked to the register took the ladies receipt gave her cash because she paid with cash and I paid with credit she took my receipt and just threw it away and said have a nice day so I believed she was gonna do something in the system to refund me. it's been over a week and I'm now out of 24 dollars for no food and a horrible experience if you don't like your job choose one your happy at and gimme my money when you ever get the chance. Last note why have a business phone number you never pick up? It's in google

This is a great soul food restaurant. There are so many meat choices and sides. Everyone in the family can find something they like. The food is set up somewhat like a buffet but the staff prepares all of the plates. You stand and line and can see the food as it’s being prepared for your to go box. The food is always fresh and the portions are large. We always have left overs. The quality of the food is excellent. We always have great experiences when we eat here. The fried fish and beef ribs are a must try. The Mac and cheese is excellent. The cakes are moist and flavorful too. You’ll be sure to love it.

A friend that lives in MARYLAND recommended this place to us while visiting. It did not disappoint us. The service was great. The food was Awesomely Good. The restaurant was clean and the servers wore plastic gloves as they served us our very huge portions of food. It was also my husband bday and they sang him a happy birthday song. Everything about our first visit here was on point. We will definitely be back again.

GHETTO but the food is GREAT

There was a wait because they were busy and seemingly understaffed. The waiting area is right by the kitchen… ❗️BAD DECISION❗️

I hear one waitress talk about how she wants to (blank) somebody up & she doesn’t have time for the (redacted).

Another waitress spills a cup of sweet tea coming out of the kitchen and most of the staff walk right by it. One waiter who noticed decided to pick up and move all the ice out of the way of traffic. I referred to him as the super waiter. I wish we had him. Short light skinned and loud. He needs to train the rest of the staff. He was engaging with his tables and very warm.

A pregnant woman gets there and possibly got bad take out service and literally tried to start a fight and broke a vase. It took them 15mins to get the Asian lady to clean that up. some of the glass broke in the area of a new born. I guess the aforementioned lady does all the cleaning since she was the same one who cleaned the sweet tea from earlier and now the vase and latter cleaned off our table.

We had a rather sizable party, our waiter starts by letting us know that the bill can ONLY be split 3 ways. Also never gave us the first time welcome other tables got.

🥗🥓 The Food
That cornbread with cinnamon based and butter. Addictive. Mac & Cheese is okay for franchise mac & cheese. Yams were on the money. Crab meat was fresh salmon was perfect shrimp were nice and everything was seasoned to perfection. My plate was called the Carolina Salmon. Sweet Tea is southern and the hostess was very nice.
Once the food came out not one complain and not one unhappy person with their meal. Even a few to go containers. Peach cobbler was 3 out of 5. (It was given to me to go as asked but I think it was semi frozen)

This place is unbelievable, first walk in, the guys name “Charles “ was so nice ! He provided  the best service! ! I never see a man cool like him ! It is our first time be in the restaurant, and I think they get the traditional way to welcome to first time customers. Just prepare for that😂😂
This place is awesome! Food is delicious 😋! Definitely will go to the restaurant again!

This place has some excellent food… if it’s your first time in the establishment, the rejoicing that they give to you makes you feel extremely welcomed☺️.  The biscuits was absolute 🔥 the Mac and cheese was excellent!  It was my first time there but I will definitely have to make a return trip next time im back in the DC area!  Here’s a pic of one of the many plates our table had.  I’d share the other plates but… they were too busy eating and photo of their plates were the last thing they were thinking about 😄. The waiter even made you feel like he was a part of your family… loved the whole vibe!

TropQ is a boutique ice cream parlor. Organic and allergen aware. They prep the ice cream for you right before your eyes with liquid nitrogen. I had the Cinnamon one-scoop. Sweet and hit the spot. Next time I'm gonna try the tamarind! Their menu also has acai bowls and coffee. Lastly, I see they do a big custom catering business. I would love me some whisky walnut... Lol. If only it was on their in store menu...lol.
Loved the ice cream so much I went back for seconds 10 minutes after eating my first cup! Great customer service! This place is a must if you are traveling in the inner harbor!!!
Ice cream was good and Ty's dedication and passion for the trade is abundantly clear.  Will visit again and would encourage others to do the same.
Great customer service and delcious ice cream with unique flavors made right in front of me - YUM!!
They have great service and the sugar free ice cream I got was amazing!!!

Unique neighborhood tea shop with so much more to offer.  I had a delicious Matcha Maca and a Spinach pastry (so good, just the right amount of heat).  Loved the variety of bagged teas and accessories.  Can’t wait to try more.  Nice seating area outside.

Calabash is the best! When you come to Calabash, the team will ask you how you’re feeling to help direct you to a healing drink. They also have TONS of goodies to purchase for use at home, too.

Their outdoor patio is a perfect way to spend an afternoon.

Great reprieve from the hustle and bustle. Wonderful place for small kids AND fur babies- hard feat in a small space. Delicious, affordable, healthy and staff is beyond helpful and efficient.  Great experience!!!!

At Calabash Tea & Tonic each customer is given a warm reception.  Recommendations for both food and beverage are expertly offered upon request based upon what you seek.  Many customers purchased products for personal use as well as as gifts during my late December 2022 visit.  This warm and inviting spot is a favored gathering location for locals to sip, chill, eat and relax and accommodates group gatherings as well.

What a vibe! I was not prepared for how much I'd like this spot. Came in for a tea to go (person behind the counter was SUPER helpful, btw), left with a bag of tea for the fall season and some soap. Can't wait to come back and try more. In the meantime, I'm going to shop the online store!
Tasty chicken wings, plus nice service! I would love to support this mom-and-pop shop around the corner.

Prices are too high! I understood why it was soo high last year & in the beginning of the year but things around the world are back open & supply &’demand isn’t as high as before. So drop the prices back to what it used to be or at least offer coupons like before. We trying soo hard to keep you guys in business but you’re robbing us at this point. 3 wings & fries shouldn’t be $15.00

I’ve been eating here since I was 8 years old, I’m 26 now. & for the last 2 years prices have shy rocket. & they don’t even offer free things if u order over uh certain amount! It’s sad & not fair how they over charging us! I hate it! 4 wings with fries shouldn’t be $16! You guys are gonna lose him customers, if u can’t satisfy customers why not just close down for good

This restaraunt could be better the food is hit or miss not always consistent. They are very stubborn about correcting their mistakes. Instead they blame you and give you a hard way to go no matter how respectful you are when conveying the mistake they made. Use to be our favorite family carryout but not anymore.

I stopped by earlier & when I heard them prices i left out & went around the corner to Jerry’s Carryout. Sammy’s keeps upping prices & I can’t afford it anymore. I tried to order uh half of steak & cheese wit fries & ended up having to pay over $13! But at other Carryout’s it’s only $9.00 .
Do better Sammy’s you guys lost uh customer & I’ve been coming for 9 years

Best restaurant out of all of my visits to the DMW. I was recommended by a real foodie and this place did not disappoint. I love seafood and they definitely hit the spot! I had the  smoked salmon dinner, my friend had the 2 crab cake dinner (worth $50!), and my boyfriend had the southwest bowl (no meat). All very delicious!

Whatever else you choose to order, start with the smoked fish sampler. It's enough for a whole meal for one or as an appetizer for several. Diverse flavors, including candied salmon (a favorite). Diverse crowd, too. Great rooftop spot!

Unfortunately,  as much as I wanted to love this place, I couldn't. The food had no seasoning and the drinks were blah.

The outside environment has a great vibe! But, everything else was wayyyyy below standards.

I wouldn't recommend this place.

This is my first time at this spot. Look it was some good food. The only the Lox and bagel is better at another local place but that's here nor there right now. However the price for the food is amazing. The portion sizes are good enough to fill you up and it had me full. I did try the wings, salmon burger, po boy, and chicken sandwich. This far I'm liking it. So I have to come back for more. The staff was really friendly and the ambience is nice as well. There's a fire pit outside that people can sit at. Also the parking was not too bad. Remember it's DC and parking will always be an issue. I'm definitely going to go back and update my review.

Very disappointed with the service at Ivy City. I went to an event and ordered the $15 calamari from their menu, which totaled $24 with the tax and automatic gratuity. It was the skimpiest, driest calamari I have ever had! I expressed my frustration to the bartender, who knew, based on the looks of the calamari, that it was a very tiny amount and didn't look appetizing. He then went to get me another order and after waiting 15 additional minutes it came out the same. There was more batter than calamari. Very dry and bland. The bartender got the manager Peter who came out and basically said that’s how it comes. I told him I didn’t want it, he took it and never came back. Left no direction on what to do with the bill and didn’t offer anything different.

My friend also ordered the chicken sandwich which tasted like it was fried in fish oil. It literally tasted like cat fish. We were told they don't mix chicken and fish, but something wasn't right because all 3 of my friends said it tasted like fish. So maybe it was mistakenly fried in fish oil, or the oil was very old, but we sent it back from some of their grilled wings which were also very dry and bland.

One star because the bartender was nice!

This place is beyond disgusting and needs to be shut down i ordered a whole steak and cheese fries and 2 egg rolls for pick up when I got there the man in the back started making a steak and cheese... so I was watching I didn’t know if it was mine or not..and it was. I watched him cut the bread open with his bare hands and put it on the grill,  grabbed the onions with his bare hands and put them on the grill, wiped his hands on his pants wiped his nose. Then kept looking back to see who was paying attention. I was!!! I asked for my money back only issue is I paid with a card and now have to wait for my money. Then the lady kept ignoring me. She said her manager was coming after me waiting for 20 min no one shows up, I ride down the street and came back she tried to say the manager had came and left. DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY HERE.

I've been going here a few years now. The food is typically splendid 👌. The rib tips are savory and chewy and the General Taos chicken is plentiful. You generally get more food than you bargain for which is not such a terrible thing.

This place is hit or miss.  The "Drunken Noodles" dish is good.  However, today, I ordered chicken wings for mom and I.  The wings were so small that they looked as if they were taken from Cornish hens.  Not only were the wings super small, but they were super tough, and tasted as if they were at least a couple days old.  I pulled what meat I could pull from the wings to make chicken soup.  I wouldn't suggest buying chicken wings from Panda of DC.

Pros: Open late, Fast delivery, and Temperature of the Cons: The person that took my order over the phone was so RUDE that I almost hung up.The shrimp & broccoli and orange chicken was decent. The spring and egg rolls were dry. I won't order from there ever again.

Horrible.  Ordered Cashew chicken and I got peanut chicken.  Ordered apple Pie and it came with pure liquid running out and no apple.  Inside of the crust not baked.  flour was raw.  Food was horrible could not be eaten.  Please do not waste your money.  In addition, the chicken taste like powder and definitely, not the texture of chicken meat.  The rest was peppers, onion, squash, baby corn and corn starch gravy.  Overall, I wished I could give it zero star.  My co-workers were ordering and invited me to join them, but never again.  Uncooked food and surely, I do not know the texture of this meat.  It is in the trash.  They may keep the money.  I wouldn't even call to complain and use any more of my energy talking about this horrible mess.

I have driven by MGM countless times. I made it a point to stop by today and I am mad at myself for waiting so long.  We ordered breakfast and really enjoyed it. The ham is amazing and freshly cooked. The pancakes and waffles were so soft and tasty.  The potatoes were well seasoned and delicious. Only thing that would make it better is if they had mimosas. They have beer so fingers crossed many one day.

First time visiting MGM Roast Beef for breakfast. Wow, I came hungry and had a big plate. It was that, a big plate split in two different boxes. $11.99 for the most expensive breakfast choice and I had to take some home. I recommend that you choose French toast as our group preferred it over the waffle but I do want to come back for some blueberry pancakes. The service for dine in is counter order, get a buzzer and a short wait for some fresh food.
P.S. don’t sleep on breakfast it ends at 10:30…but don’t worry Lunch goes 10:30-3pm and it deserves another visit and I’ll drop a review for that soon too!
The meats are fantastic! Do a great job of making sandwiches out of them. Buy a used car next door if you stop in on a Saturday.

I walked in with high expectations.  just couldn't decide what to get. I didn't have much time on my lunch break so I asked for a large order of fries, topped with bacon, cheese, and gravy. Similar to Poutine but with the MGM twist. It was Amazing!. Had all my coworkers try it. Even though it's not on the menu, get you some MGM fries with bacon cheese and gravy! 10/10 highly recommend 👌

This place has delicious sandwiches. The company I worked for a few years ago would often order the sandwich platters for the office. I always looked forward to those days. I've visited this place twice and the food was on point both times. I'd definitely be a more frequent customer if I lived in the area.

I loved going to this place that was located in Adams Morgan. Halfway between concert hall and cafeteria. They have not been able to maintain the essence in the new location. However, they still have a pretty interesting agenda of events, a fantastic atmosphere, and affordable prices. The Drag Queen's night is quite good, fun, and with many points of clever and spicy humor.
